X-ray photoelectron spectra (XPS) were carried out to further identify the surface functional state and components of the N, P-CDs. XPS survey shows that carbon (C 1s, 285 eV), nitrogen (N 1s, 400 eV), and oxygen (O 1s, 532 eV) elements are all contained in the CDs (Fig. 3
                         (a)). Meanwhile, trace quantities of phosphorus (P) with P 2p at 153 eV are also observed. N 1s and P 2p are the evidence that N and P have been successfully doped in N, P-CDs. Elemental analysis also conﬁrms the elemental composition of the CDs: carbon (62.1 wt %), nitrogen (24.7 wt %), oxygen (10.8 wt %), phosphorus (2.4 wt %) (Table 1
                        ).
